    • Method Detail

      • onCaptureSequenceCompleted

        void onCaptureSequenceCompleted(CameraCaptureSession session,
                                CameraCaptureSequenceId cameraCaptureSequenceId,
                                long lastFrameNumber)
        This method is called when a capture sequence is completed. Once this is invoked, no further calls to CameraCaptureSession.CaptureCallback.onNewFrame(org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.external.hardware.camera.CameraCaptureSession, org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.external.hardware.camera.CameraCaptureRequest, org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.external.hardware.camera.CameraFrame) will be made.
        Parameters:
        session - The session returned by Camera.createCaptureSession(<any>)
        cameraCaptureSequenceId - A sequence ID returned by CameraCaptureSession.startCapture(org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.external.hardware.camera.CameraCaptureRequest, org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.external.hardware.camera.CameraCaptureSession.CaptureCallback, <any>)
        lastFrameNumber - The last frame number (returned by CameraFrame.getFrameNumber() in the capture sequence, or CameraFrame.UnknownFrameNumber if no frames have been observed.
        See Also:
        CameraFrame.getFrameNumber(), CaptureFailure.getFrameNumber(), CameraFrame.getCaptureSequenceId(), CaptureFailure.getSequenceId()
